$interpreted: Tindoiimu: Sophie! Hanbei! ...Eidatyr!!
Tindoiimu: (This is a disaster. I can barely see a thing, and I'm separated from the others...)
Tindoiimu: (I can feel my energy sapping away, much faster than normal... I'm just not used to this cold...)
Tindoiimu: (Of all the moments, why now...!)
Tindoiimu: Phew... ngh...
Tindoiimu: (I can feel my body temperature dropping, I've got to get out of here...)
Tindoiimu: (But... Where should I go...)
Tindoiimu: (Didn't I just pass by here...?)
Tindoiimu: (Isn't this... the place I was earlier? No... I can't tell, it all looks the same...)
Tindoiimu: (I... I've no idea where to go now...)
Tindoiimu: (I followed Sophie and Eidatyr here... If I'm all on my own...)
Uzziah: Step aside.
Tindoiimu: You're...!
Tindoiimu: (...He's so strong... He took that monster down so easily...!)
Tindoiimu: (I know what I just saw. That power was just like the kind that Juan-Yun was using...)
Uzziah: ...What are you doping around for? Stand up already. There'll be more monsters here before you know it.
Tindoiimu: ...Tell me.
Uzziah: Huh?
Tindoiimu: Who are you!? Just who the hell sent you!?
Uzziah: You overestimate yourself. You know very well that you and I are not the same.
Tindoiimu: So... So what... I... want to know... the truth...
Uzziah: The truth?
Tindoiimu: ...Who are you? Who are you with? ...Who is he... Why are you doing this...
Uzziah: ......
Uzziah: ...I know no companions. I don't know who it is you seek, but it must be one of my enemies.
Tindoiimu: An enemy? You clearly possess the same powers as each other...
Uzziah: ...Perhaps they look the same to your eyes. In any case, you'd do well not to involve yourself.
Uzziah: I'll say no more to you. Go rejoin your companions. If we should ever meet again... run as fast and as far as you can.
Tindoiimu: ...I'm not going anywhere until you answer me!
Tindoiimu: This... isn't... over...
Uzziah: ...Why do you insist with such stubbornness? You've barely a drop of strength left.
Uzziah: It's not too late. Return to your path...
Tindoiimu: What path!!
Tindoiimu: You've taken everything from me. Everything! I've nowhere left to go!
Tindoiimu: I want to know the truth! You owe me that, at the very least!!
Uzziah: (...She's passed out.)
Uzziah: (It's bitterly cold. Not to mention these monsters... She probably won't last long if I leave her here...)
Uzziah: (Should I take her with me? ...No, I'd be influencing her consciousness...)
Uzziah: (Then again, she's not giving up. She'll never stop demanding answers of me...)
Uzziah: (...Enough. She's far from the only casualty of the sect... The top priority must be to prevent their next steps...!)
Tindoiimu: You've taken everything from me. Everything! I've nowhere left to go!
Uzziah: (...Even so, didn't I once say those exact words, too...? Indeed... So long ago...)
Tindoiimu: Ngh...
Tindoiimu: Where... am I...
Tindoiimu: (It's him? I have to ask him—)
Uzziah: ...*sigh*.
Tindoiimu: Stop!
Tindoiimu: Ow...! Wait... Wait for me...!
Uzziah: ...*sigh*.
Tindoiimu: ......
Uzziah: ...Hmph.
Tindoiimu: ...You... You've stopped for me...?
Uzziah: ......
Tindoiimu: Will you... help me find my way back?
Uzziah: ......
Tindoiimu: ...I'll catch up!
